         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>ARCHER HPC Facility - Service Provision</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>PR120039</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="72250000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The ARCHER service comprises the hardware, Computational Science and Engineering (CSE) support, Service Provision (SP) support, hardware.</P>
               <P>Accommodation support and external users UKRI, as managing agent for the national HPC facility is extending (a period of up to 15 months) the existing service provision contract for ARCHER which includes:</P>
               <P>— co-ordinate and interface with the elements of the ARCHER service,</P>
               <P>— to deploy, configure, maintain and upgrade the system software, system administration tools and user environments as they are made available,</P>
               <P>— front line service and user engagement (via a help desk),</P>
               <P>— service availability and reliability,</P>
               <P>— scheduling and allocation of resources,</P>
               <P>— user registration and access.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_RANGE_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">
               <LOW>1650000</LOW>
               <HIGH>1850000</HIGH>
            </VAL_RANGE_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="72253000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="72260000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="72611000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKM73"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>UKRI, as managing agent for the national HPC facility is extending the existing 5 years contract by a period of up to 15 months to ensure continuity of the existing ARCHER facility until plans for a replacement ARCHER2 have been agreed, approved and procured.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
                  <D_OUTSIDE_SCOPE/>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>Due to delays in the procurement of a replacement facility (ARCHER2) the existing ARCHER facility is being extended until such time that plans for ARCHER2 are agreed, approved and a replacement facility procured. The Service Provision (SP) element of the ARCHER facility cannot be separated from the hardware and associated services without serious disruption to the ARCHER service and significant additional cost.</P>
                     <P>Were CSE and SP services not to extend in line with the hardware, the ARCHER service would not be able to function. The loss of the compute capability would affect over 6 500 regular users of the ARCHER Service and the disruption of over 800 research projects currently dependent on the computing power of the ARCHER machine.</P>
                     <P>Any new SP provider cannot be sourced currently as the nature of the SP service is such that a change in provider on the same technology platform would cause significant disruption to the ARCHER service.</P>
                     <P>In addition, agreement and approval of plans for ARCHER2 would not be able to be procured by the end of the existing contract.</P>
                     <P>The extension to this contract is being made under Regulation 72 (1) (b) of the public contract Regulations 2015.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
